===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fa|en}} {{term|sc=fa-Arab|پنجاب||[Land of] the Five Rivers|tr=panj-âb|lang=fa}}, from {{term|sc=fa-Arab|پنج|tr=panj|lang=fa||five}} and {{term|sc=fa-Arab|آب||tr=âb|water|lang=fa}}, referring to five rivers of the {{w|Punjab region}}: the [[w:Jhelum River|Jhelum]], the [[w:Chenab River|Chenab]], the [[w:Ravi River|Ravi]], the {{w|Sutlej}} and the [[w:Beas River|Beas]].

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A geographical region in [[South Asia]], divided (by the {{w|Radcliffe Line}}) between India and Pakistan. Pakistani Punjab includes the [[West Punjab|(West) Punjab Province]] and parts of the [[Islamabad Capital Territory]]; Indian Pubjab includes [[East Punjab|(East) Punjab State]] and some other territories.

